thread.title: Ice divers take New Year's Day plunge at Lake Minnetonka
thread.title_full: Ice divers take New Year's Day plunge at Lake Minnetonka

title: Ice divers take New Year's Day plunge at Lake Minnetonka
text:
Ice divers take New Year's Day plunge at Lake Minnetonka About 800 braved the icy waters to ring in the new year in Excelsior. January 1, 2017 — 6:58pm Prev 1 /10 Next Elizabeth Flores – Star Tribune 
Gallery: Rebecca Boynton plunged into the 32 degree Lake Minnetonka for the 27th Annual ALARC Ice Dive on New Year's Day in Excelsior. About 800 people braved the icy waters to ring in the new year and to contribute to the Wounded Warrior Project. Elizabeth Flores – Star Tribune 
Gallery: A pair plunged into the 32 degree Lake Minnetonka for the 27th Annual ALARC Ice Dive on New Year's Day in Excelsior. Elizabeth Flores – Star Tribune 
Gallery: Warmly dressed spectators took pictures as jumpers plunged into Lake Minnetonka for the 27th Annual ALARC Ice Dive on Sunday. Elizabeth Flores – Star Tribune 
Gallery: Participants lined up on the dock as for the 27th Annual ALARC Ice Dive on Sunday into Lake Minnetonka in Excelsior. Elizabeth Flores – Star Tribune 
Gallery: ALARC co-founder Bill Wenmark, an avid marathoner, cheered as jumpers plunged into Lake Minnetonka for the organization's annual on Sunday in Excelsior. About 800 braved the icy waters to ring in the new year and to contribute to the Wounded Warrior Project. Elizabeth Flores – Star Tribune 
Gallery: A trio in tie-dye jumped into Lake Minnetonka during the 27th Annual ALARC Ice Dive on New Year's Day in Excelsior. The event included prizes for the two best costumes. Elizabeth Flores – Star Tribune 
Gallery: Tish Borgen of New Hope, MN, held onto a rosary as she was nervous about jumping into the 32 degree Lake Minnetonka for the 27th Annual ALARC Ice Dive, Sunday, January 1, 2017 in Excelsior, MN. About 800 braved the icy waters to ring in the new year and to contribute to the Wounded Warrior Project. Elizabeth Flores – Star Tribune 
Gallery: Brianne Olson of Carver plunged into Lake Minnetonka with her daughter Pieper Olson, 7, center, and Maddie Dufrane, 7, right, during the ALARC Ice Dive, Sunday in Excelsior. Elizabeth Flores – Star Tribune 
Gallery: Dressed as Wonder Woman, Kris Barneby, right, plunged into the 32 degree Lake Minnetonka alongside Joe Jeppesen, left, for the 27th Annual ALARC Ice Dive, Sunday, January 1, 2017 in Excelsior, MN. About 800 braved the icy waters to ring in the new year and to contribute to the Wounded Warrior Project. Elizabeth Flores – Star Tribune 
Gallery: Spectators watched as jumpers plunged into the 32 degree Lake Minnetonka for the 27th Annual ALARC Ice Dive, Sunday, January 1, 2017 in Excelsior, MN. About 800 braved the icy waters to ring in the new year and to contribute to the Wounded Warrior Project.
